<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,153,1007]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,872,899]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Comments.</emphasis>
Compared with the other species that have completely papillate face, antennal sockets usually on a distinct but low shelf, setose eyes and second tergite with a posterior transverse groove, pterostigma nearly symmetrical, unlike in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[367,469,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[367,469,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[485,643,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veracruzus">
<emphasis box="[485,643,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. veracruzus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[700,849,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis box="[700,849,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; mesoscutum with ‘shoulder stripes’ along notaular lines and frontal orbits light brown and indistinct, unlike in 
<taxonomicName box="[819,1010,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicaraguensis">
<emphasis box="[819,1010,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. nicaraguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
